  <wpt lat="40.75095" lon="-96.636417">
    <time>2026-07-07T17:30:00</time>
    <name>GCBR8YK</name>
    <desc>Diners and Dives #91 by peteach!, Event Cache (1.0/1.0)</desc>
    <url>https://coord.info/GCBR8YK</url>
    <urlname>Diners and Dives #91</urlname>
    <sym>Geocache</sym>
    <type>Geocache|Event Cache</type>
    <groundspeak:cache id="10471201" archived="False" available="True" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1">
      <groundspeak:name>Diners and Dives #91</groundspeak:name>
      <groundspeak:placed_by>peteach! and starsharon </groundspeak:placed_by>
      <groundspeak:owner id="5787200">peteach!</groundspeak:owner>
      <groundspeak:type>Event Cache</groundspeak:type>
      <groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container>
      <groundspeak:attributes>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute>
      </groundspeak:attributes>
      <groundspeak:difficulty>1.0</groundspeak:difficulty>
      <groundspeak:terrain>1.0</groundspeak:terrain>
      <groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country>
      <groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state>
      <groundspeak:short_description html="True">&lt;b&gt;07 July 2026, 17:30 - 19:15&lt;/b&gt;</groundspeak:short_description>
      <groundspeak:long_description html="True">&lt;p&gt;Please join starsharon and peteach! for a progressive supper at different Diners &amp;amp; Dives in or near Lincoln and beyond. &amp;nbsp;We will rotate host duties every month.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Location for Tuesday, July 7, 2026:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Mulberry&amp;#39;s BBQ, 6125 Apples Way, #209, Lincoln NE.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please provide a &amp;#39;Will Attend&amp;#39; log so we can get a head count for our selected location of the month.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Connect with other geocachers to ask for a tip or two on your caches without a &amp;#39;SMILEY&amp;#39;, trade/share travel bugs or just enjoy the company of fellow geocachers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No purchase is necessary to attend the event&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We hope to see you there. &amp;nbsp;A recurring monthly Geocaching Event in Lincoln and occasionally in the surrounding area that is open to everyone. Local and out-of-town geocachers are welcome and encouraged to attend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://nebraskache.com/"&gt;&lt;img height="95" src="https://img.geocaching.com/9102f957-c986-41b5-acdb-a076bd017129.jpg" width="187" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://nebraskache.com/"&gt;Hosted By A Nebraskache Member&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/107321656812/"&gt;&lt;img height="58" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/19b6196d-f1d8-431b-9201-f4069d107ada_l.png" width="183" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As the geocache owner, I ensure that this links to a local geocaching group that is active in the community and contributing to geocaching in positive ways. This link has not been checked by Geocaching HQ or by the reviewer.&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description>
      <groundspeak:encoded_hints>Great ribs</groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      <groundspeak:logs>
        <groundspeak:log id="1370721333">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-07-08T01:35:10Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="1411659">starsharon + Hubbie</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Fun and delicious event.</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1370720380">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-07-08T01:16:10Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="1693430">BRE1</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Nice food. Great company. TFTC. </groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1370720105">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-07-08T01:11:01Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="815525">kc0aoo</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Nice crowd. Thanks for hosting </groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1370720092">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-07-08T01:10:32Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="1246261">kyle1993</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Had great time </groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1370969392">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-07-08T00:30:00Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="28905599">Shelbyyy919</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">I wouldn't know any of these people at all if it weren't for Geocaching. It's pretty obvious what our common interest that even brought us together is. It's nice to be able to get together and catch up and talk about geocaching AND everything else that may be happening on our lives and such. 
I drive an hour out of my way to a town that I don't even live in to have a monthly chance to catch up with my fellow geocachers that I'd normally never get a chance to see. Thanks for having events like this and keeping them up so we are able to see each other and catch up and talk about whatever comes up while representing and enjoying our one common interest that got us here in the first place. 

Thanks for the event. 👍🏻</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
      </groundspeak:logs>
    </groundspeak:cache>
  </wpt>
